      %h3
        Motivation
    .medium-6.cell.text-left
      %p 
        A great number of data sets exist but are underutilized and difficult to discover. Making data discoverable helps to promote open science practices and increases reproducibility of research. Providing researchers tools to highlight and disseminate their data sets as well as identify other existing data sets could lead to decreased duplication of effort and cost, new opportunities to collaborate, validation for past studies, new questions and research ideas, and the potential for increased future grant funding. 
      %p 
        Datasets are an important research product, requiring time, money, and hard work to generate and maintain. Improved tools and strategies to enhance dissemination, discovery, reuse, and enable other improvements are sorely needed. DataCat can help!
    .medium-1.cell
  %hr
  .grid-x.grid-margin-x.align-middle
