      %h3
        Future Work
    .medium-6.cell.text-left
      %p DataCat will be linked to axillary sources such as:
      %ul
        %li
          Research data management platforms
        %li
          Research Information Systems
        %li
          Grants
        %li
          Publications
        %li 
          Research studies
      %p Other planned enhancements include:
      %ul
        %li
          Development of resources and materials to support stakeholders with deposit, management, and preservation of data assets across interdisciplinary research topics.
        %li 
          Integration of 
          %a{:href => "https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/26978244"}
            FAIR data standards 
          (Findable, Accessible, Interoperable, and Reusable), supplemented with additional principles of Traceable, Licensed, and Connected 
          %a{:href => "https://zenodo.org/record/203295#.Wi62TLQ-fUJ"}
            (FAIR-TLC).
        %li
          Assessment of licensing to evaluate a resource's data license for use and reuse. 
        %li
          A post-deposit “peer review” feature similar to the strategy used in PubMed Commons will be incorporated.
    .medium-1.cell
